        <p> {{ page.overview.intro|raw }} Hotel, to the left or right of it is suitable for swimming or snorkeling. Well that can be a fun stay, my first thought was. I stayed in the room and Basti went to the diving base to get ready. I had just read the first pages when Basti was back in the door "There is still a girl to snorkel. Want to go with? Would have 30 minutes to get ready". Hm ok, he started again and I get out of the sleeping clothes, freshly made, sunscreen on it, bathing clothes on and off. </p>
        <p> He already came towards me because I was probably hanging after time, but I fight with our patio door lock again. Since Hanschi had told us yesterday that it is so -free, I didn't think about a suit and went on the boat right away. On the boat it turned out that Bianca, the other snorkeling girl, and her accompaniment are Hamburgers. So of course we got into conversation. The journey to the "Blue Water" diving area went quickly and we were in the water. Unfortunately, the area was not very suitable for snorkeling, since the water depth was quite huge. Well and then there were the jellyfish! Yes exactly, jellyfish - so much too "jellyfish"! The water was quite full of it and we both snorkelers had all the trouble getting out of the number. It burned here and there, but by no means as violent as in Anda. I went back on the boat relatively early because there was nothing to be seen anyway and enjoyed the silence of the sea until the divers were back up. </p>
