        <p> Arrived at the base again, we complained to Hanschi. This was very amazed that the jellyfish were there and apologized several times. Well he really can't do anything for! I now hopped in the pool and then relaxed in the sun. Basti had an appointment with the other Hamburg woman for a second dive at noon and so we stayed in the resort. Shortly before Basti had to go to the second dive, I was armed with a towel and book towards the beach. "Unfortunately" I ran into the girls and they persuaded me to snorkel on a second round, this time with a suit. Alone she wouldn't want etc. Weiber !!!!! </p>
        <p> Hanschi gave me a suit, I daked back to the room and changed. The relaxed afternoon was gone. This time we drove a little further, the jellyfish could have nothing to do, but there was nothing to see again. The water was too deep again. The waves became more and more over time and I noticed that I got strange to me. Damn, I had also forgotten the tablets! Unfortunately, staying in the sea doesn't help me and so I climbed on board again. The boat guide helped me out of the suit and the width of the horizon belonged to me! I was sick and the divers could not show up. At some point he called my fellow swimmer on board because he said he had seen the divers. Hm we drove and drove and hidden behind two more boats I saw them too. So he can never have seen her in life. That must have been communication from ship to ship! </p>
